\begin_layout Point
Portal is a video game released in 2007 by Valve Software,
 and it was a very influential game for video game design.
 As a puzzle game,
 it is very important that it teaches its workings to the players,
 so that they understand all the pieces and need to figure out how to put the pieces together.
 The game is widely considered to do so rather well,
 with a lot of development time being spent in addressing this matter,
 and in a bold move,
 especially for the time,
 spends a lot of game time explaining the mechanics â€“ it's said that about 50% of the game is tutorial,
 which was quite revolutionary,
 as a lot of games at the time had really short and crummy tutorials and a lot of people would just skip past them because they were boring...
 And yet,
 Portal players would spend approximately 3 hours of game time playing a tutorial,
 often not even noticing it for what it was.
 Surely there is a big parallel to be drawn here!
